The paper deals with rateless codes, which are a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses encoding and decoding algorithms, which fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of generating matrices and linear codes suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the application of rateless codes to communication networks implies a connection to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
